Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} on medium heat. Heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium high heat (this is for the cod later on). While the pans heats up, peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest and halve the @lime{½}(zested and halved).

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%can} and @sweetcorn{150%g} in the same #sieve{}. Season the @cod fillets{2} with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the garlic and @Caribbean style jerk{1%tsp} to the saucepan, stir and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Pour in the @water{75%ml} and stir in the @vegetable stock powder{1%tsp}. Stir in the @rainbow chard{150%g} a handful at a time and simmer for ~{2%minutes}.

Stir in the corn and blackbeans, simmer until the chard is tender, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Add the @steamed coconut basmati rice{1%pack} to the pan, break it up with a #spoon{}, stir together with everything else and cook until the rice is piping hot, another ~{1-2%minutes}.

Meanwhile, lay the cod in the frying pan and fry until cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} each side.

> IMPORTANT: The cod is cooked when opaque all the way through.

Add the @honey{15%g} to the pan and squeeze in half the lime juice. Cook for ~{1%minute} more. Remove from the heat.

Stir the lime zest through the rice, taste and add salt and pepper if you feel it needs it.

Spoon the rice into #bowls{} and spoon over the cod and the lime honey mixture. Serve with a grind of pepper and any remaining lime cut into segments alongside for squeezing over.